-- Jamaica Wins Men’s 400-Meter Relay Gold in World Record Time
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-11T20:04:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-11/jamaica-wins-men-s-400-meter-relay-gold-in-world-record-time.html
Jamaica  won the men’s 400-meter
relay at the London Olympics in a world record time of 36.84
seconds. The victory gives Usain Bolt his third gold of the
games.  The U.S. won the silver medal and Canada won the bronze.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  